{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 22:20:07.292305", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission successful.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"server_access_router\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"ospf_area_misconfiguration\"]\n\nNotes:\n- The server_access_router is advertising the backend server subnet 10.200.0.0/24 into OSPF (network 10.200.0.0/24 area 0) and the subnet is directly connected on br0, causing backend servers to be reachable from host subnets. This violates the intended design that backend servers be reachable only via the load balancer. Consider removing or filtering the advertisement of 10.200.0.0/24, applying appropriate ACLs/VRF segmentation on the server_access_router, or enforcing server access via the load balancer.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2252, "output_tokens": 163, "total_tokens": 2415, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1792}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
